## .dockerignore — standard exclusions for .NET Docker builds
## Prevents local build artefacts from overwriting the restore/build output
## generated inside the container.  Without this, copying src/ or tests/
## after `dotnet restore` would replace the container's obj/project.assets.json
## with a potentially stale local copy, causing NETSDK1064.

# Build artefacts
**/obj/
**/bin/

# IDE / OS noise
**/.vs/
**/.idea/
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# NuGet local caches
**/*.user
**/*.suo
**/.nuget/

# Test / benchmark result artefacts (large; not needed in image)
BenchmarkDotNet.Artifacts/
benchmark-results/
output/
reports/

# Git
.git/
.gitignore

# Docker files themselves (not needed inside the image)
Dockerfile*
.dockerignore

# CI / benchmark scripts not needed inside the image
# (run-equivalency.sh and run-benchmarks.sh ARE needed — do not exclude *.sh globally)
#benchmark-tutorial-comparison.sh
#run-benchmarks.sh
*.md


